<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">The gloves can be gotten fairly easily by anyone about 24th lvl or higer. Radiant is a 21-23 lvl spawn(watch out...he is a rogue) and if you stand around CT for more than half an hour you'll here a shout from someone asking if an enchanter wants the loot. The glowing gloves are a little harder...but they are 24th-26th lvl mobs. Easily within group range to hunt. Hell, if you can break the spawn..you can solo the camp for a good half hour before the fast spawn rate catches up with you (i.e. Beguile your ass off.) Note on the shadowed men...the gloves will be a decent camp. The shadowed men drop items for at least 4 other quests and they are ALL rare drops. Took me 2 hours to get what I needed (I played haste bitch to a higher lvl group to get them the first time...). But..at 24th and a half level I got my gloves. And I like em. Ac 6? Cha +3, Agi +3 ? Cool. Str +3? Nice bonus..I need the extra str because I hang out in CT a lot and carry a lot of FS around. +3 mana? Eh....<br>
 Good luck to you all   <p>

       -Sardos Dreamweaver (25th lvl Enchanter Of Tunare)</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
